verbose_text: Interestingly, Zhu et al. have recently identified a cytochrome b 5 / b 5 reductase fusion protein, NAD (P) H cytochrome b 5 oxidoreductase (Ncb5OR), located in the lumen of the endoplasmic reticulum, which when deleted in mice results in marked decreases in hepatic levels of palmitoleic and oleic acid, suggesting a role for this protein in electron transport to SCD1.
evidence: levels of palmitoleic and oleic acid
